<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,1418,1839]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1418,1443]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Scutellum at least anteriorly densely longitudinally reticulate, meshes often indistinctly elongate. Female antenna with three funicular segments not clearly separated from clava, which seems funicle 2-segmented and clava 3-segmented (
<emphasis box="[437,477,1492,1515]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">e.g.</emphasis>
, 
<figureCitation box="[496,567,1490,1515]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1577,1599]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,697,1555]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,697,1555]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 9. Pediobius metallicus (Nees, 1834). a: female, body in dorsal view; b: female, body in lateral view; c: male, body in dorsal view; d: male, body in lateral view; e: female, fore wing; f: male, antenna; g: female, antenna; h: female, fore leg; i: female, hind leg. Scale bar: a – d, 0.5 mm; e: 0.4 mm; f – i, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/375768/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[552,567,1491,1515]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="9.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="g" value="9.0">9</quantity>
</figureCitation>
g). Male antenna filiform, never with a differentiated clava (
<emphasis box="[1281,1321,1492,1515]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">e.g.</emphasis>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1340,1411,1490,1515]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1577,1599]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,697,1555]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,697,1555]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 9. Pediobius metallicus (Nees, 1834). a: female, body in dorsal view; b: female, body in lateral view; c: male, body in dorsal view; d: male, body in lateral view; e: female, fore wing; f: male, antenna; g: female, antenna; h: female, fore leg; i: female, hind leg. Scale bar: a – d, 0.5 mm; e: 0.4 mm; f – i, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/375768/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
f). Scrobal grooves in female always meeting below the frontofacial sutures.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,1418,1839]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,405,1562,1587]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Species included.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Boucek" box="[414,596,1562,1587]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Boucek, Z. (1965 a) Studies of European Eulophidae, IV: Pediobius WALK. and two allied genera (Hymenoptera). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 36, 5 - 90." type="journal article" year="1965" yearSuffix="a">Bouček (1965a)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName box="[711,814,1562,1587]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Pediobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eubius">
<emphasis box="[711,814,1562,1587]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P. eubius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex and 
<taxonomicName box="[979,1125,1562,1587]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Pediobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallicus">
<emphasis box="[979,993,1564,1587]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1009,1125,1562,1587]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">metallicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the 
<taxonomicName box="[1208,1309,1564,1587]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Pediobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="epigonus">
<emphasis box="[1208,1309,1564,1587]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">epigonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group, but also divided this group into two subgroups, the 
<emphasis box="[686,769,1598,1623]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">eubius-</emphasis>
subgroup and the 
<taxonomicName box="[969,1070,1599,1622]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Pediobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="epigonus">
<emphasis box="[969,1070,1599,1622]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">epigonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-subgroup. The 
<emphasis box="[1249,1331,1598,1623]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">eubius-</emphasis>
subgroup includes 
<taxonomicName box="[253,356,1634,1659]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Pediobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eubius">
<emphasis box="[253,356,1634,1659]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P. eubius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex, 
<taxonomicName authority="Thomson" authorityName="Thomson" box="[479,760,1634,1659]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Pediobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigritarsis">
<emphasis box="[479,626,1636,1659]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P. nigritarsis</emphasis>
(Thomson)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Boucek (Boucek 1965a)" authorityName="Boucek (Boucek" authorityYear="1965" box="[819,1259,1634,1659]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Pediobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polanensis">
<emphasis box="[819,969,1634,1659]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P. polanensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[979,1259,1634,1659]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Boucek, Z. (1965 a) Studies of European Eulophidae, IV: Pediobius WALK. and two allied genera (Hymenoptera). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 36, 5 - 90." type="journal article">Bouček (Bouček 1965a)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<taxonomicName box="[1325,1426,1636,1659]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Pediobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="epigonus">
<emphasis box="[1325,1426,1636,1659]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">epigonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- subgroup includes 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker" authorityName="Walker" box="[364,602,1670,1695]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Pediobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="epigonus">
<emphasis box="[364,493,1671,1694]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P. epigonus</emphasis>
(Walker)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Boucek" authorityName="Boucek" box="[614,845,1670,1695]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Pediobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabratus">
<emphasis box="[614,750,1670,1695]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P. glabratus</emphasis>
Bouček
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[858,1001,1670,1695]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Pediobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallicus">
<emphasis box="[858,872,1671,1694]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[886,1001,1670,1695]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">metallicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Boucek (Boucek 1965a)" authorityName="Boucek (Boucek" authorityYear="1965" box="[1016,1436,1670,1695]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Pediobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oviventris">
<emphasis box="[1016,1154,1671,1694]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P. oviventris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[1162,1436,1670,1695]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Boucek, Z. (1965 a) Studies of European Eulophidae, IV: Pediobius WALK. and two allied genera (Hymenoptera). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 36, 5 - 90." type="journal article">Bouček (Bouček 1965a)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and also those species described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dawah" box="[567,731,1706,1731]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Dawah, H. A. (1988) Taxonomic studies on the Pediobius eubius complex (Hymenoptera: Chalcidoidea: Eulophidae) in Britain, parasitoids of Eurytomidae in Gramineae. Journal of Natural History, 22, 1147 - 1171. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222938800770731" type="journal article" year="1988">Dawah (1988)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation box="[790,1024,1706,1731]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Dawah, H., Al-Haddad, F. &amp; Jervis, M. (2002) Morphological and biological characterization of three closely related species of Pediobius Walker (Hymenoptera: Eulophidae). Journal of Natural History, 36, 423 - 433. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930010023501" type="journal article">
Dawah 
<emphasis box="[878,936,1706,1731]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
(2002)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hansson" box="[1036,1217,1706,1731]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Hansson, C. (2006) Pediobius sasae (Hymenoptera Eulophidae), a new species from galls on dwarf bamboo (Sasa nipponica) in Japan. Zootaxa, 1249, 37 - 45." type="journal article" year="2006">Hansson (2006)</bibRefCitation>
included a distinct species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hansson" authorityName="Hansson" box="[245,440,1743,1766]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Pediobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sasae">
<emphasis box="[245,335,1743,1766]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P. sasae</emphasis>
Hansson
</taxonomicName>
, in the 
<taxonomicName box="[521,594,1742,1767]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Pediobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eubius">
<emphasis box="[521,594,1742,1767]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">eubius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group. We follow 
<bibRefCitation author="Boucek" box="[806,985,1742,1767]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Boucek, Z. (1965 a) Studies of European Eulophidae, IV: Pediobius WALK. and two allied genera (Hymenoptera). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 36, 5 - 90." type="journal article" year="1965" yearSuffix="a">Bouček (1965a)</bibRefCitation>
and include them in the 
<taxonomicName box="[1260,1361,1743,1766]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Pediobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="epigonus">
<emphasis box="[1260,1361,1743,1766]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">epigonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group despite the possibilities of different separation for its members. Besides, we add a newly described species, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Pediobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prominentis">
<emphasis box="[1415,1429,1780,1803]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,284,1815,1838]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">prominentis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which seems closer to 
<taxonomicName box="[551,652,1814,1839]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Pediobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eubius">
<emphasis box="[551,565,1815,1838]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[579,652,1814,1839]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">eubius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
